[{"id":"b18f8484a2e1696cc14b06246c752a4a","from":"Lookout Mobile Security","from_email":"feedback@email.lookout.com","to":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","to_list":[{"name":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"Security Alert: XcodeGhost iOS malware found. What you should do","date":"2015-09-21T22:36:54.000Z","formatted_date":"Sep 21, 2015","formatted_time":"10:36 PM","body":" \n\nResearchers recently found a piece of iOS malware called XcodeGhost that has been embedded into a number of applications in the Apple App Store, without the app developers\u2019 knowledge. These unsuspecting apps include popular apps such as WeChat and CamCard.\n\nWhat can XcodeGhost do?\n\nXcodeGhost is a piece of malware that can steal data and potentially trick people into providing their personally identifiable information. The XcodeGhost creators were able to repackage a tool used by legitimate iOS and OSX developers to create apps. When those developers created their apps using this tampered-with tool, they unknowingly inserted malware into their applications.\n\n\n\nThe malware made it into several applications that were live in the Apple App Store.\n\nDoes Lookout protect me?\n\nWe are providing you with a \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=f3a2d063787565778fc9e8408d45b37c1f41fa8c0948e8d14d2be625ba51e32f300a51cd0128d764 \nlist of all affected applications  so you can remove them from your device immediately. Unfortunately, Apple has recently eliminated the ability for third party developers (like Lookout) to see which apps are running on your device, which limits our ability to alert you about malicious apps, but we will continue to update this list to make sure you have the most up-to-date information.\n\nHow do I protect my iOS devices?\n\n\n.;\n\n Be aware of the applications pushing dialog boxes to your screen and don\u2019t enter personal information without first being aware of who is asking for it.\n\n\n.;\n\n If you have any of the apps on your phone (listed on our blog), you should delete them immediately and wait until the app developer has released a new version with a patch.\n\n\n.;\n\n If one of these apps is running on your device, we also recommend that you change your Apple account password and be wary of any suspiciousemails or push notifications to your device asking for personal information.\n\n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=f3a2d063787565773f0976ff428c5c836f0d57a26e64ccf4a456aad2606400345b70a69bdb05a80f \nSee the Impacted Apps \n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=f3a2d0637875657779ae47c6aa172a236a689bb169dec6e42a3c256a7c4deafbc0818db8a324a06e \nLearn more about Lookout \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=f3a2d06378756577bfd5dfb0d6b6ac74921ab1ebeb2cf3a001871115619e303404c29d68fec0c75c \n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=f3a2d063787565779a8858d180af60fa4950ca4c2162fef9d4b7195763c6807a5cc59f13f27f626f \n\n\u00a9 2015 Lookout, Inc. \u2219 One Front St. Suite 2700 \u2219 San Francisco, CA 94111\n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=f3a2d063787565773128c4294c62be0a760524642dbba487df2e46f923f00f734db5df5e5d6d38e2 \nManage Profile  \u00b7 \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=f3a2d063787565773b74e290ac68fe0d91bdfbfe92ccde96728bfebfd1305d028bb3531c1a529522 \nPrivacy  \u00b7 \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=f3a2d06378756577ce9a4f5bea0eba9caaa29bad2564c4c90d4e7e71c40afc9d0ecb307a3b9ab1bc \nTerms and Conditions  \u00b7 \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=f3a2d063787565770f893fb03382a29b1d779a8c81e1037db720c206646070e614a92a8e43600b5d \nUnsubscribe \n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=f3a2d063787565774be1d5531aa30521fe2d1bc9913e9f5f4ea7fcdceae2ce1c06a8bcfc7b063ff0 \n\n\n \n","body_html":"</body></html><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n  <head>\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\" />\n    <title></t